 "cells": [
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"nbformat\": 4,\n",
    " \"nbformat_minor\": 5,\n",
    " \"metadata\": {\n",
    "  \"kernelspec\": {\n",
    "   \"display_name\": \"Python 3\",\n",
    "   \"language\": \"python\",\n",
    "   \"name\": \"python3\"\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  \"language_info\": {\n",
    "   \"name\": \"python\",\n",
    "   \"version\": \"3.11.0\"\n",
    "  }\n",
    " },\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"# Mushroom Edibility Classification\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Classification Project 21 of 100** — Predict edible vs poisonous mushrooms.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"EDA -> preprocessing -> baseline -> LazyPredict -> FLAML -> top-3 evaluation.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 2. Project Overview\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Binary classifier for mushroom edibility using 22 categorical features from the UCI dataset (8,124 samples). Easy dataset with near-perfect separability via odor.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 3. Learning Objectives\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. All-categorical dataset (22 features)\\n\", \"2. OneHotEncoder for low-cardinality categoricals\\n\", \"3. Odor as dominant predictor\\n\", \"4. Accuracy, F1, ROC-AUC evaluation\\n\", \"5. LazyPredict and FLAML benchmarking\\n\", \"6. Asymmetric error costs in safety-critical ML\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 4. Problem Statement\\n\", \"\\n\", \"> Predict edible or poisonous from 22 categorical mushroom attributes.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Recall on poisonous class is most critical — FN is potentially fatal.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 5. Why This Project Matters\\n\", \"\\n\", \"| Stakeholder | Impact |\\n\", \"|---|---|\\n\", \"| Foragers | Life-or-death identification |\\n\", \"| ML learners | All-categorical, perfect separability |\\n\", \"| Safety-critical ML | Asymmetric error costs |\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 6. Dataset Overview\\n\", \"\\n\", \"| Property | Value |\\n\", \"|---|---|\\n\", \"| Kaggle slug | uciml/mushroom-classification |\\n\", \"| Rows | 8,124 |\\n\", \"| Features | 22 categorical |\\n\", \"| Target | class (e=edible, p=poisonous) |\\n\", \"| Balance | ~52% edible, ~48% poisonous |\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 7. Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- Kaggle: uciml/mushroom-classification\\n\", \"- License: CC0. From Audubon Society Field Guide (1981).\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 8. Environment Setup\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\n\", \"for pkg in [\\\"lazypredict\\\",\\\"flaml\\\",\\\"kagglehub\\\",\\\"xgboost\\\",\\\"lightgbm\\\"]:\\n\", \"    try: importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n\", \"    except ImportError: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,\\\"-m\\\",\\\"pip\\\",\\\"install\\\",\\\"-q\\\",pkg])\\n\", \"print(\\\"Environment ready.\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 9. Imports\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"import os, warnings, glob\\n\", \"import numpy as np, pandas as pd\\n\", \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt, seaborn as sns\\n\", \"from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\\n\", \"from sklearn.preprocessing import OneHotEncoder, LabelEncoder\\n\", \"from sklearn.compose import ColumnTransformer\\n\", \"from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\\n\", \"from sklearn.dummy import DummyClassifier\\n\", \"from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier\\n\", \"from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier, GradientBoostingClassifier\\n\", \"from sklearn.metrics import (accuracy_score, precision_score, recall_score, f1_score,\\n\", \"    roc_auc_score, ConfusionMatrixDisplay, RocCurveDisplay, classification_report)\\n\", \"from lazypredict.Supervised import LazyClassifier\\n\", \"from flaml import AutoML\\n\", \"warnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\"); sns.set_theme(style=\\\"whitegrid\\\"); SEED=42\\n\", \"print(\\\"All imports loaded.\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 10. Configuration / Constants\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"KAGGLE_SLUG = \\\"uciml/mushroom-classification\\\"\\n\", \"TARGET = \\\"class\\\"\\n\", \"TEST_SIZE = 0.15; VAL_SIZE = 0.15; SEED = 42; FLAML_BUDGET = 60\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Target: {TARGET}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 11. Dataset Download or Loading\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"import kagglehub\\n\", \"try:\\n\", \"    path = kagglehub.dataset_download(KAGGLE_SLUG)\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"Downloaded to: {path}\\\")\\n\", \"except Exception as e:\\n\", \"    raise RuntimeError(f\\\"Download failed: {e}\\\")\\n\", \"csv_files = glob.glob(os.path.join(path,\\\"**\\\",\\\"*.csv\\\"), recursive=True)\\n\", \"df_raw = pd.read_csv(csv_files[0])\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Shape: {df_raw.shape}\\\")\\n\", \"df_raw.head()\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 12. Data Validation Checks\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"print(f\\\"Missing: {df_raw.isnull().sum().sum()}\\\")\\n\", \"df = df_raw.copy()\\n\", \"const_cols = [c for c in df.columns if df[c].nunique() <= 1]\\n\", \"if const_cols:\\n\", \"    df = df.drop(columns=const_cols)\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"Dropped constant: {const_cols}\\\")\\n\", \"dupes = df.duplicated().sum()\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Duplicates: {dupes}\\\")\\n\", \"assert TARGET in df.columns\\n\", \"print(f\\\"\\\\nTarget:\\\\n{df[TARGET].value_counts()}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 13. Exploratory Data Analysis\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(5,4))\\n\", \"df[TARGET].value_counts().plot.bar(ax=ax, color=[\\\"forestgreen\\\",\\\"crimson\\\"])\\n\", \"ax.set_title(\\\"Edible vs Poisonous\\\"); ax.set_xticklabels([\\\"Edible\\\",\\\"Poisonous\\\"], rotation=0)\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"if \\\"odor\\\" in df.columns:\\n\", \"    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10,4))\\n\", \"    ct = pd.crosstab(df[\\\"odor\\\"], df[TARGET], normalize=\\\"index\\\")\\n\", \"    ct.plot.bar(stacked=True, ax=ax, colormap=\\\"RdYlGn_r\\\")\\n\", \"    ax.set_title(\\\"Edibility by Odor\\\"); plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"feat_cols = [c for c in df.columns if c != TARGET]\\n\", \"card = pd.Series({c: df[c].nunique() for c in feat_cols}).sort_values(ascending=False)\\n\", \"print(\\\"Feature cardinalities:\\\"); print(card)\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 14. Target Analysis\\n\", \"\\n\", \"~52% edible, ~48% poisonous. Odor alone separates classes almost perfectly.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"print(f\\\"Edible: {(df[TARGET]=='e').mean():.1%}  Poisonous: {(df[TARGET]=='p').mean():.1%}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 15. Train / Validation / Test Split\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"le = LabelEncoder()\\n\", \"X = df.drop(columns=[TARGET]); y = le.fit_transform(df[TARGET])\\n\", \"X_tmp, X_test, y_tmp, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=TEST_SIZE, random_state=SEED, stratify=y)\\n\", \"X_train, X_val, y_train, y_val = train_test_split(X_tmp, y_tmp, test_size=VAL_SIZE/(1-TEST_SIZE), random_state=SEED, stratify=y_tmp)\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Train: {X_train.shape}  Val: {X_val.shape}  Test: {X_test.shape}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 16. Preprocessing Strategy\\n\", \"\\n\", \"All categorical — OneHotEncoder for all features.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"cat_cols = X_train.columns.tolist()\\n\", \"preprocessor = ColumnTransformer(transformers=[\\n\", \"    (\\\"cat\\\", OneHotEncoder(handle_unknown=\\\"ignore\\\", sparse_output=False), cat_cols)\\n\", \"], remainder=\\\"drop\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Cat features: {len(cat_cols)}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 17. Feature Engineering\\n\", \"\\n\", \"HAS_FOUL_ODOR: foul/pungent/creosote flag.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"def eng(d):\\n\", \"    d = d.copy()\\n\", \"    if \\\"odor\\\" in d.columns:\\n\", \"        d[\\\"HAS_FOUL_ODOR\\\"] = d[\\\"odor\\\"].isin([\\\"f\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"c\\\",\\\"s\\\",\\\"m\\\"]).astype(str)\\n\", \"    return d\\n\", \"X_train=eng(X_train); X_val=eng(X_val); X_test=eng(X_test)\\n\", \"cat_cols = X_train.columns.tolist()\\n\", \"preprocessor = ColumnTransformer(transformers=[\\n\", \"    (\\\"cat\\\", OneHotEncoder(handle_unknown=\\\"ignore\\\", sparse_output=False), cat_cols)\\n\", \"], remainder=\\\"drop\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Features: {X_train.shape[1]}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 18. Baseline Model\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"results = {}\\n\", \"for name, clf in [(\\\"Dummy\\\",DummyClassifier(strategy=\\\"most_frequent\\\",random_state=SEED)),\\n\", \"                  (\\\"DecisionTree\\\",DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=3,random_state=SEED)),\\n\", \"                  (\\\"RF\\\",RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100,random_state=SEED,n_jobs=-1))]:\\n\", \"    pipe = Pipeline([(\\\"pre\\\",preprocessor),(\\\"clf\\\",clf)])\\n\", \"    pipe.fit(X_train, y_train); yp=pipe.predict(X_val)\\n\", \"    r={\\\"Accuracy\\\":accuracy_score(y_val,yp),\\\"F1\\\":f1_score(y_val,yp),\\\"Recall\\\":recall_score(y_val,yp)}\\n\", \"    if hasattr(clf,\\\"predict_proba\\\"): r[\\\"ROC-AUC\\\"]=roc_auc_score(y_val,pipe.predict_proba(X_val)[:,1])\\n\", \"    results[name]=r; print(f\\\"{name}: {r}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 19. LazyPredict Benchmark\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"X_train_lp=preprocessor.fit_transform(X_train); X_val_lp=preprocessor.transform(X_val)\\n\", \"lazy=LazyClassifier(verbose=0,ignore_warnings=True,random_state=SEED)\\n\", \"models_lp,_=lazy.fit(X_train_lp,X_val_lp,y_train,y_val)\\n\", \"models_lp.head(15)\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 20. FLAML AutoML Run\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"automl=AutoML()\\n\", \"automl.fit(X_train_lp,y_train,task=\\\"classification\\\",metric=\\\"f1\\\",time_budget=FLAML_BUDGET,seed=SEED,verbose=0)\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Best: {automl.best_estimator}\\\")\\n\", \"yp_fl=automl.predict(X_val_lp)\\n\", \"results[\\\"FLAML\\\"]={\\\"Accuracy\\\":accuracy_score(y_val,yp_fl),\\\"F1\\\":f1_score(y_val,yp_fl)}\\n\", \"print(results[\\\"FLAML\\\"])\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 21. Top 3 Model Selection\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"try:\\n\", \"    from lightgbm import LGBMClassifier; has_lgbm=True\\n\", \"except ImportError: has_lgbm=False\\n\", \"try:\\n\", \"    from xgboost import XGBClassifier; has_xgb=True\\n\", \"except ImportError: has_xgb=False\\n\", \"top3={}\\n\", \"if has_lgbm: top3[\\\"LightGBM\\\"]=LGBMClassifier(n_estimators=200,learning_rate=0.1,max_depth=4,random_state=SEED,verbose=-1,n_jobs=-1)\\n\", \"else:\\n\", \"    from sklearn.ensemble import ExtraTreesClassifier\\n\", \"    top3[\\\"ExtraTrees\\\"]=ExtraTreesClassifier(n_estimators=200,random_state=SEED,n_jobs=-1)\\n\", \"if has_xgb: top3[\\\"XGBoost\\\"]=XGBClassifier(n_estimators=200,learning_rate=0.1,max_depth=4,random_state=SEED,verbosity=0,n_jobs=-1,eval_metric=\\\"logloss\\\")\\n\", \"else:\\n\", \"    from sklearn.ensemble import AdaBoostClassifier\\n\", \"    top3[\\\"AdaBoost\\\"]=AdaBoostClassifier(n_estimators=200,random_state=SEED)\\n\", \"top3[\\\"GradBoosting\\\"]=GradientBoostingClassifier(n_estimators=200,learning_rate=0.1,max_depth=3,random_state=SEED)\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Top 3: {list(top3.keys())}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 22. Final Training and Evaluation of Top 3\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"X_tr_t=preprocessor.fit_transform(X_train); X_te_t=preprocessor.transform(X_test)\\n\", \"labels=[\\\"Edible\\\",\\\"Poisonous\\\"]\\n\", \"final={}\\n\", \"for name,mdl in top3.items():\\n\", \"    mdl.fit(X_tr_t,y_train); yp=mdl.predict(X_te_t); ypr=mdl.predict_proba(X_te_t)[:,1]\\n\", \"    final[name]={\\\"Accuracy\\\":accuracy_score(y_test,yp),\\\"Precision\\\":precision_score(y_test,yp),\\\"Recall\\\":recall_score(y_test,yp),\\\"F1\\\":f1_score(y_test,yp),\\\"ROC-AUC\\\":roc_auc_score(y_test,ypr)}\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"\\\\n{name}:\\\"); print(classification_report(y_test,yp,target_names=labels))\\n\", \"pd.DataFrame(final).T\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"fig,axes=plt.subplots(1,len(top3),figsize=(5*len(top3),4))\\n\", \"if len(top3)==1: axes=[axes]\\n\", \"for ax,(n,m) in zip(axes,top3.items()):\\n\", \"    ConfusionMatrixDisplay.from_predictions(y_test,m.predict(X_te_t),ax=ax,cmap=\\\"Blues\\\",display_labels=labels); ax.set_title(n)\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 23. Error Analysis\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"bm=list(top3.values())[0]; ypb=bm.predict(X_te_t)\\n\", \"fn=(y_test==1)&(ypb==0); fp=(y_test==0)&(ypb==1)\\n\", \"print(f\\\"FN (poisonous called edible): {fn.sum()} — CRITICAL\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"FP: {fp.sum()}\\\")\\n\", \"if fn.sum()==0 and fp.sum()==0: print(\\\"Perfect classification.\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 24. Interpretation and Business Insight\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Odor is the dominant feature. Perfect accuracy achievable. Never rely solely on ML for mushroom identification.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 25. Limitations\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Only 2 genera\\n\", \"2. Perfect separability — unrealistic\\n\", \"3. No images\\n\", \"4. 1981 data\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 26. How to Improve This Project\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Newer UCI dataset (2023, 61k+)\\n\", \"2. Image classification\\n\", \"3. Extract decision rules\\n\", \"4. Cost-sensitive model\\n\", \"5. SHAP analysis\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 27. Production Considerations\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- Never deploy as sole identification\\n\", \"- FN cost >> FP cost\\n\", \"- Confidence thresholds needed\\n\", \"- Monitor for new species\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 28. Common Mistakes\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Not noticing odor solves it\\n\", \"2. Complex models when tree suffices\\n\", \"3. Not dropping constant columns\\n\", \"4. Treating codes as numeric\\n\", \"5. Not focusing on recall\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 29. Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Train with only odor — accuracy?\\n\", \"2. Minimum depth tree for 100%?\\n\", \"3. Drop odor — which features compensate?\\n\", \"4. Cost-sensitive model (FN=1000x FP)\\n\", \"5. Decision tree rules vs mycology\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 30. Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\", \"\\n\", \"| Aspect | Detail |\\n\", \"|---|---|\\n\", \"| Task | Binary — mushroom edibility |\\n\", \"| Dataset | 8,124, 22 categorical |\\n\", \"| Difficulty | Easy — deterministic |\\n\", \"| Key insight | Odor separates classes |\\n\", \"\\n\", \"All-categorical classification, safety-critical ML, full pipeline.\"]\n",
    "  }\n",
    " ]\n",
    "}\n"
   ],
   "id": "c6a9dace3ed66777"
  }
 ]
